                                                                                                3.11 OMB Memorandum M-16-03, Fiscal Year 2015-2016 Guidance on Federal
                                                                                                     Information Security and Privacy Management Requirements
                                                                                                OMB Memorandum M-16-03 notes that, in early FY 2015, OMB and the National Security
                                                                                                Council (NSC) staff created a quarterly cybersecurity assessment organized according to the
This publication is available free of charge from: http://dx.doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-175A




                                                                                                functions in the NIST Framework for Improving Critical Infrastructure Cybersecurity (Identify,
                                                                                                Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover) and associated outcomes to comprehensively assess
                                                                                                agency cybersecurity performance. The assessment builds on the existing foundation of FISMA
                                                                                                metrics and the Cybersecurity Cross Agency Priority (CAP) 32 goals, and is reviewed by agency
                                                                                                senior leadership. Moving forward, the Memorandum states that this assessment will be the
                                                                                                cornerstone initiative for how OMB measures Federal agency cybersecurity performance.




